        <num>CC 3018</num>
        <heading>3018.  Disclosed mandate; undisclosed principal</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3018.  Disclosed mandate; undisclosed principal
A mandatary who enters into a contract and discloses his status as a mandatary, though not his principal, binds himself personally for the performance of the contract.  The mandatary ceases to be bound when the principal is disclosed.</p>
        </content>
